Description: Semiconductor devices (for example, diodes, transistors, semiconductor-based transducers); photosensitive semiconductor devices, including photovoltaic cells whether or not assembled in modules or made up into panels; light-emitting diodes (LED), whether or not assembled with other light-emitting diodes (LED); mounted piezo-electric crystals; parts thereof:
Diodes, other than photosensitive or light-emitting diodes (LED)
With a maximum current of 0.5 A or less
With a dissipation rate of less than 1 W
With an operating frequency not less than 100 MHz
With an operating frequency not less than 30 MHz
Thyristors, diacs and triacs, other than photosensitive devices
Photosensitive semiconductor devices, including photovoltaic cells whether or not assembled in modules or made up into panels; light-emitting diodes (LED):
Photovoltaic cells not assembled in modules or made up into panels
Crystalline silicon photovoltaic cells of a kind described in statistical note 10 to this chapter
Photovoltaic cells assembled in modules or made up into panels
Crystalline silicon photovoltaic cells of a kind described in statistical note 10 to this chapter
Quartz designed for operating frequencies of:
Exceeding 1 MHz, but not exceeding 5 MHZ
Exceeding 5 MHZ, but not exceeding 20 MHz
